The paper deals with the Dominating Set problem in geometric intersection graphs, which is a topic in computational geometry (cs.CG). The problem is also a classic problem in parameterized complexity theory, which falls under the category of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also involves the study of semi-algebraic sets, which is a topic in algebraic geometry and computational complexity, and thus could be categorized under cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). Additionally, the paper discusses the complexity of the problem in terms of graph theory, which could fall under cs.CC (Computational Complexity) or cs.GT (Graph Theory).
